section.section:
"Chemical warfare material" means any of the following:
Adamsite (phenarsazine chloride);
GA (Ethyl-N, N-dimethyl phosphoramidocyanidate);
GB (Isopropyl methyl phosphonofluoridate);
GD (Pinacolyl methylphosphonofluoridate);
H, HD (Bis(2-chloroethyl) sulfide);
HT (60 percent HD and 40 percent T (Bis[2(2-chloroethyl- thio)ethyl]ester));
L (Dichloro(2-chlorovinyl)arsine);
T (2-2' Di (3-chloroethylthio)-diethyl ether); or
VX (O-ethyl-S-(2-diisopropylaminoethyl) methyl phosphonothiolate).
